Retrieves occurrence data from NBN Atlas within a specified buffer around given longitude and latitude

Source: R/get_nbn_data.R
get_nbn_buffer.Rd

Retrieves occurrence data from NBN Atlas within a specified buffer around given longitude and latitude

Usage

get_nbn_buffer(lon, lat, radius = 1, n = 10000)

Arguments

lon

numeric Longitude in decimal degrees

lat

numeric Latitude in decimal degrees

radius

numeric Buffer radius in kilometers, default is 1 km

n

numeric Maximum number of occurrences to retrieve, default is 10,000

Value

data frame containing occurrence information within the buffer

Examples

get_nbn_buffer(-1.5, 52.0, 2)
